eceive a pay of rupees eight thousand plus a special pay of rupees five hundred per mensem. A Vice- Chairman shall reee've a pay of rupees eight thousand per mensemﾂｷ A member shall re- ceive a pay in the scale of Rs. 7300-100-7600 per mensem: Provided that in the case of an appoint- ment a$ Chairman, Vice-Chairman or a person who has retired as a Judge of a High Court or who has retired from service under the Central Government or a Mate Goverument and who is in receipt of or has received or has become entitled to receive any retirement benefits by way of pension and or gratuity, employer's contribution to the Contributiory Provident Fund or other fonns of retirement benefits, the pay shall be reduced by the gross amount of pension and pension equivalent of service gratuity or employer's contribution to the Contributory Provident Fund or any other form of retire- ment benefits, if any, but excluding pension equivalent of retirement gratuity, drawn or to he drawn by him.¥" -- 6 of 8 -- 3. In the said rules, for rule 4, the following rwe shall be subst:iuted, namely :- ¥"4. Dearn ess Allowance and City Compen sa tory Allowance.-The Chairman, a ViceﾂｷChairﾂｷ man and a Member shall receive Dearness Allowance and CIty CompensalOry aliowan‾e appropriate to their pay at the rates adlDlsﾂｷ sible to Group 'A' Officers of the Central Government draw¥"ng a pay in the scale of Rs. 73()()¥"100ﾂｷ7600 or above, as the case may be,¥" 4. After rule 15 of the said mles, the followmg rule s hall be inserted, namely :- ¥" 15A. Notwithstanding anything contained ‾ rules 4 to 15 of the said rules, the condIﾂｷ tions of service and other perquisites availﾂｷ able to the Chairman and Vice-Cha'rman of the Mallarashtra Administrative Tribunal shall be the same as admissible to a serving Judge of a High Court as contained in the High Court Judges (Cond:tions of Service) 3 Act 1954 (28 of 1954) and High Court Judges ([ravelling Allowances) RuI,s, 1956. [No, p, 13022i4,91ﾂｷAT] R ﾂｷ RAMANI, Jt, Secy. EXPLANATORY MEMORANDUM The Central Government has decided to implement the decisions taken on the recommendations 01 the ,Fourth Central Pay Commiss;on relating to revision of pay in respect of the Central Civil Services Group 'A', Since all the appointments of Chairman, Vice.Chair man and Members in the Maharashlra Administrative Tribunal have been made with effect from 8th July, 1991, these rules are being given effect from that date, It 's cert'fied that no Chairman, Vice-Chairman aod Member of the Maharashtra Administrative Tribunal is likely to be affected adversely by this notification being given retrospective effect. Footnote :-The Pr'nc'pa! rules were published vide GSR 1157(E) dated the 21st October, 1986. Printed by the Manager, GO¥¥-ﾂ｣. ot Ind ia Pr eSl, RiD&: Road , New DeIluﾂｷll0064 and Publ i,h d hy tho ('ontro Uor of Pu b li cali oDi, Delhiﾂｷ110054, 1992 -- 7 of 8 -- -- 8 of 8 --",
